      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are explicitly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the primary metrics used by FDA to evaluate spinal implant mechanical performance. They are directly relevant to the clinical risk of construct failure under physiological loading."
